  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legitimate\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most include:\n- Intentionally disguising the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Transferring or converting property knowing it represents criminal activity\n- Concealing or disguising the true nature of criminal property\n\nThe specific details and precise legal language depend on the particular laws of each country.",
